When booting your OpenBSD system, you have probably noticed the boot prompt.

<blockquote><pre>
boot>
</pre></blockquote>

d117 3
a119 8
<a href="http://man.openbsd.org/boot.8">boot(8)</a>
man page.

<p>
If no commands are issued, the boot loader will automatically try to boot
<tt>/bsd</tt>.
If that fails, it will try <tt>/obsd</tt>, and if that fails, it will try
<tt>/bsd.old</tt>.
