<small>$OpenBSD: faq8.html,v 1.225 2011/01/18 16:31:37 joshe Exp $</small>
@


1.225
log
@Add Conkeror to browser list.
"oki" landry@@
@
text
@d1095 6
a1100 2
Mg is a micro Emacs-style text editor included in OpenBSD.  Micro means that it's small
(Emacs is very large!) For the basics, read the 
d1102 4
a1105 12
manual page and the 
<a href="http://www.openbsd.org/cgi-bin/cvsweb/~checkout~/src/usr.bin/mg/tutorial?rev=HEAD;c">tutorial</a>,
as included with the source code.
If you have installed the <a href="faq5.html#BldGetSrc">source code</a>,
you will find the tutorial file at <tt>/usr/src/usr.bin/mg/tutorial</tt>,
otherwise you can download the file from the above link and use it.

<p>
Note that since mg is a small Emacs implementation, which is mostly
similar to the text editor features of Emacs 17, it does not implement
many of Emacs' other functionality (including mail and news
functionality, as well as modes for Lisp, C++, Lex, Awk, Java, etc...).
d1434 1
a1434 1
