@a56 2
<li><a href= "#wwwsolaris"  >8.18 - Why did www.openbsd.org used to 
  run on Solaris?</a>
a1145 16
<a name= "wwwsolaris"></a>
<h2>8.18 - Why did www.openbsd.org used to run on Solaris?</h2>

<p>
Although none of the developers think it is particularly relevant, this
question comes up frequently enough in the mailing lists that it is
answered here.  <i>www.openbsd.org</i> and the main OpenBSD ftp site were
hosted at a <a href="http://sunsite.ualberta.ca">SunSITE</a> at the University of Alberta, Canada.   These sites
were hosted on a large Sun system, which had access to lots of storage
space and Internet bandwidth.  The presence of the SunSITE gave the
OpenBSD group access to this bandwidth.  This is why the main site used
to run there.
<p>Things have changed, and the main www and ftp sites run OpenBSD
these days.

<p>
d1418 1
a1418 1
