A user sets up an OpenBSD box as a firewall and gateway
to their internal home network, mapping all their internal computers 
to one external IP using 
<a href="faq6.html#NAT">NAT.</a>
They may also use it as an outbound mail
relay.  They follow the installation guidelines, and are very happy with
the results, except for one thing -- every time they try to attach to the
box in any way, they end up with a two minute delay before things happen.
