<h2>8.19 - I'm having problems with my PCI devices being detected in OpenBSD 2.8.</h2>
d1143 5
a1147 2
There exists a condition in OpenBSD 2.8 where some machines might not detect some PCI devices properly, or might freeze while detecting multiple NIC's in one machine. This is the fault of PCIBIOS, and involves a simple workaround to make work properly.
Simply enter the boot time configuration and disable PCIBIOS. An example is below:
d1156 8
a1163 3
