@d83 5
a87 5
Only i386 arch has virtual terminal capabilities. You can also use virtual
terminals when using X. For example, If you start X on term 1, and switch
with [ctrl]-[alt]-[F2] to term 2, X will seem to disapear and will not
come back by simply switching back to term 1. You must [ctrl]-[alt]-[F5]
to get your X display back.
d268 6
d462 1
